      • relax

        public boolean relax​(Regions.RegionInfo current,
                     Regions.RegionInfo next)
        Checks the argument and decreases next's distance if the new distance created by getNewValue(Region, Region, Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo, Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo, int[]) is smaller than the old one. Subclasses should usually not overwrite this method, but getNewValue(Region, Region, Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo, Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo, int[]) .
        Specified by:
        relax in interface Regions.Metric
        Returns:
        true if nextRecord's distance was decreased
        See Also:

      • getNewValue

        protected abstract boolean getNewValue​(Region r1,
                                       Region r2,
                                       Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo current,
                                       Regions.MultiDimensionalInfo next,
                                       int[] newValues)
        Subclasses should implement this method and return their new distance value encoded in newValues. newValue[3] is pre-initialized with the potential.
        Parameters:
        newValues - An array with four elements that should hold the result like {dist, plus, realDist, pot}.
        Returns:
        false if the distance of next should not be decreased
